TY  - JOUR
TI  - The Cyclicality of Sales, Regular, and Effective Prices: Business Cycle and Policy Implications: Comment
AU  - Gagnon, Etienne
AU  - López-Salido, David
AU  - Sockin, Jason
AB  - [Coibion, Gorodnichenko, and Hong (2015) argue that the CPI underestimates the deceleration in consumer prices during economic downturns because the index fails to account for the reallocation of consumer spending from high-price to low-price stores. We show that their conclusion hinges on some nonstandard methodological choices, including an aggressive censoring of price adjustments and a treatment for missing observations that can leave out some of the price variation. Under our preferred methodology, the regression results no longer indicate that greater store switching during downturns is a statistically or economically significant phenomenon.]
